.TH "afu_read" 9 "afu_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
afu_read \- perform a read on the context for any event
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" afu_read
.BI "(struct file *file "  ","
.BI "char __user *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ","
.BI "loff_t *off "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file" 12
File associated with the adapter context.
.IP "buf" 12
Buffer to receive the data.
.IP "count" 12
Size of buffer (maximum bytes that can be read).
.IP "off" 12
Offset.
.SH "RETURN"
size of the data read on success, -errno on failure
